Besides easy access to firearms for young people, a hovering systemic problem still haunts American society and triggers more gun violence-hate. Be it racial or religious or ideological, hate kills. Hatred has long been an illness in America. The American people are not unfamiliar with hate crimes. And hate crimes in the U.S. hit a 12-year high in 2020, reported by Federal Bureau of Investigation (FBI). And when hate meets guns, hate crimes could become much deadlier. CGTN brings you special coverage on "America at Gunpoint".